<div id="pf1391" class="pf w4 h138" data-page-no="1391"><div class="pc pc1391 w4 h138"><div class="t m1078 x15 h4 y22ad ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">14 </div><div class="t m5 x26 h4 y22ad ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mb41 x59 h4 y20a3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SABBATH SCHOOL LESSON QUARTERLY </div><div class="t mf1b x15 h4 y1734 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6: 9). In order that the Spirit might come in such a capacity </div><div class="t m1055 x15 h4 yb2c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as the Comforter, it was necessary that Jesus should be glori-</div><div class="t m11ef x15 h4 y1a7c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fied (John 7: 38, 39), through His death and resurrection </div><div class="t mbfb x27 h4 y19a2 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 12: 23, 24). The Son of God was with the Father </div><div class="t m1291 x15 h4 y16df ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">before He came to this world (John 17: 5) ; but when He </div><div class="t m1a8b x15 h4 y20b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">became the Son of man, a new manifestation appeared, &quot;God </div><div class="t md24 x15 h4 yc8e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with us&quot; (Matt. 1: 23). The man, Jesus of Nazareth, was </div><div class="t mc59 x15 h4 y11e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">anointed with the Holy Spirit (Acts 10: 38) ; it was &quot;through </div><div class="t m1a28 x15 h4 y179a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the eternal Spirit&quot; that Christ offered Himself to God (Heb. </div><div class="t mc46 x15 h4 y4fd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9: 14) ; the risen Lord is identified with the Spirit (2 Cor. </div><div class="t m1539 x92 h4 y1992 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3: 17) ; and thus the Holy Spirit is the representative of the </div><div class="t m2765 x15 h4 y19f3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">new order, and in this sense &quot;was not given&quot; until after the </div><div class="t m1408 x15 h4 y16af ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">death and resurrection of Christ. </div><div class="t m2226 x7d h4 y16fa ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• </div><div class="t m88f x32